broke) and of Dublin by Henry II, who granted the city to the burgesses of Bristol. The surname was Gaelicized as <b>de Carduibh</b>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Amabil","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>amabilis</i> ‘lovable’ via Old French. Although now very rare in the English-speaking world, this name lies behind the much commoner name   Annabel   and also   Mabel .  It gained some currency from being borne by the character Amabel Rose Adams in  Angela Thirkell's  Barsetshire Chronicles (  1933  onwards)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Amabil Cardiff was born about 1170, in Cardiff Cathedral Saint David, Glamorgan, Wales as the daughter of Richard de Cardiff. She married Thomas de Sanford. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. She died in 1205, in Whitchurch, Shropshire, England, at the age of 36."},"et":{"about 1170–1205":"umbes 1170–1205","1170–1205":"1170–1205","1166–1203":"1166–1203","1187–1234":"1187–1234","1190–1225":"1190–1225","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1203–1235":"1203–1235","1142–1180":"1142–1180","1190":"1190","about 1170":"umbes 1170","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1187":"1187","1142":"1142","1250":"1250","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","1205":"1205","1203":"1203","1225":"1225","1235":"1235","1234":"1234","Abt 1187":"umbes 1187","1199":"1199","1166":"1166","Whitchurch, Shropshire, England":"Whitchurch, Shropshire, England","South Moreton, Wallingford, Berkshire, England":"South Moreton, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sanford, Whitchurch, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Whitchurch, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sandford, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cardiff Cathedral Saint David, Glamorgan, Wales":"Cardiff Cathedral Saint David, Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1170–1205":"noin 1170–1205","1170–1205":"1170–1205","1166–1203":"1166–1203","1187–1234":"1187–1234","1190–1225":"1190–1225","1199–1250":"1199–1